findings.suggestion:
BEFORE:
if (toolName in allTools) {
  allTools[namespacedName] = toolDef
}
else {
  allTools[toolName] = toolDef
}

AFTER:
// First-come wins the short name; subsequent duplicates get server-prefixed names
if (toolName in allTools) {
  allTools[namespacedName] = toolDef
}
else {
  allTools[toolName] = toolDef
}

WHY: The first-come-wins strategy is a valid design choice but is surprising without explanation. A single comment clarifies the intent and prevents future maintainers from 'fixing' it.

